<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,286,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Caliothrips</emphasis>
Daniel
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1646,1814]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
This is one of only three genera of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName box="[714,929,1646,1670]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Panchaetothripinae">Panchaetothripinae</taxonomicName>
that involves species dependent on 
<taxonomicName box="[1337,1432,1647,1670]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
. Currently this genus includes 
<number box="[493,521,1682,1706]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="22.0">22</number>
species, and these are distributed widely around the tropics. All of them apparently breed only on leaves, with five species known to be specific to 
<taxonomicName box="[935,1026,1719,1742]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
but the others often associated with 
<taxonomicName box="[151,255,1754,1778]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
or more broadly polyphagous (
<bibRefCitation author="Mound" box="[609,927,1754,1778]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Mound, L. A., Zhang, H. - R., Bei, Y. - W. (2011) Caliothrips tongi sp. n. (Thysanoptera, Thripidae) from China, and a dubious record of North American Bean Thrips. Zootaxa, 2736, 57 - 62." type="journal article" year="2011">
Mound, Zhang &amp; Bei, 
<number box="[867,927,1754,1778]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). An identification and information system is web-available (
<bibRefCitation author="Mound" box="[323,609,1790,1814]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Mound, L. A., Paris, D., Fisher, N. &amp; Tree, D. J. (2011) World Thysanoptera - an identification and information resource. http: // anic. ento. csiro. au / thrips / [accessed 20. ix. 2011]" type="journal article" year="2011">
Mound, Paris 
<emphasis box="[482,538,1790,1814]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">et al.</emphasis>
, 
<number box="[552,609,1790,1814]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) to the species taken in 
<collectingCountry box="[878,981,1790,1814]" name="Australia" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Australia</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName box="[996,1166,1790,1814]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Caliothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graminicola">
<emphasis box="[996,1166,1790,1814]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">C. graminicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1220,1396,1791,1814]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Caliothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striatopterus">
<emphasis box="[1220,1396,1791,1814]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">C. striatopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
